revision.text:
An '''associated reproductive pattern''' is a seasonal change in reproduction which is highly correlated with a change in [[gonads|gonad]] and associated [[hormones|hormone]].<ref>Alcock, John. 2005. Animal Behavior. Sinauer Associates. {{ISBN|0-87893-005-1}}</ref>

